<subSubSection id="C3115DA56E634066FF485E3E14A49EE7" lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="276" pageId="14" pageNumber="275" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BB40E2E6E634067FF485E3E16369D97" blockId="14.[151,1437,151,645]" pageId="14" pageNumber="275">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E634067FF485E3E16439D2F" bold="true" box="[199,334,548,573]" pageId="14" pageNumber="275">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name is in honor of Dr Hitoshi Ida (Professor Emeritus, Kitasato University, School of Marine Biosciences) for his contribution to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B75AD6E634067FD115E5214059D4D" authorityName="Rafinesque" authorityYear="1810" box="[670,776,584,607]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="275" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E634067FD115E5214059D4D" box="[670,776,584,607]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="275">Epigonus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9A73DF6E634067FCCD5E5D14E19D72" box="[834,1004,583,608]" pageId="14" pageNumber="275" refId="ref19644" refString="Ida, H., Okamoto, M. &amp; Sakaue, J. (2007) Epigonus cavaticus (Teleostei: Perciformes), a new epigonid fish from Palau, western Central Pacific. Ichthyological Research, 54, 131 - 136. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 10228 - 006 - 0384 - 9" type="journal article">
Ida 
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E634067FCE25E5314909D72" box="[877,925,584,608]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="275">et al</emphasis>
., 2007
</bibRefCitation>
) and other percoid studies in the Indo- Pacific region.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF745EA66E634067FF185BAA160198F7" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1182191/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="275" startId="14.[151,250,1968,1990]" targetBox="[188,1398,697,1947]" targetPageId="14">
<paragraph id="8BB40E2E6E634067FF185BAA160198F7" blockId="14.[151,1436,1968,2021]" pageId="14" pageNumber="275">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E634067FF185BAA162C98D7" bold="true" box="[151,289,1968,1990]" pageId="14" pageNumber="275">FIGURE 11.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C0B75AD6E634067FEA55BAB16B498D4" authority="Okamoto &amp; Gon, 2018" authorityName="Okamoto &amp; Gon" authorityYear="2018" box="[298,441,1968,1990]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="275" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="idai" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E634067FEA55BAB16B498D4" box="[298,441,1968,1990]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="275">Epigonus idai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24C6F476E634067FE4C5BAB16F298D4" box="[451,511,1969,1990]" pageId="14" pageNumber="275" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E634067FE4C5BAB16F298D4" bold="true" box="[451,511,1969,1990]" pageId="14" pageNumber="275">n. sp.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, SAIAB 82171, holotype, 136.8 mm SL; A: fresh specimen; B: preserved specimen; C: radiograph.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BB40E2E6E624066FF485C8D14A49EE7" blockId="15.[151,1436,151,501]" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E624066FF485C8D152F9FA2" bold="true" box="[199,546,151,176]" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">Comparisons and Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C0B75AD6E624066FDBF5C8215D99FA2" authorityName="Okamoto &amp; Gon" authorityYear="2018" box="[560,724,152,176]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="276" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="idai">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E624066FDBF5C8215D99FA2" box="[560,724,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">Epigonus idai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to the 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B75AD6E624066FC155C83134B9FBD" baseAuthorityName="Giglioli" baseAuthorityYear="1880" box="[922,1094,152,176]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="276" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="constanciae">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E624066FC155C83134B9FBD" box="[922,1094,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">E. constanciae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group by having a pungent opercular spine (Okamoto 2012). 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B75AD6E624066FD975CA715B89FC6" authorityName="Okamoto &amp; Gon" authorityYear="2018" box="[536,693,188,212]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="276" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="idai">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E624066FD975CA715B89FC6" box="[536,693,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">Epigonus idai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is unique in this species group in having 4–5 tiny projections on the symphysis of lower jaw (
<figureCitation id="133012AB6E624066FE565CC5153D9FEA" box="[473,560,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURE6" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1874,1896]" captionTargetBox="[226,1344,1400,1852]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[226,1360,1400,1852]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE6. Ventral viewof symphysis of lowerjaw.A:Epigonus bispinosusn. sp., SAIAB35606, 1of 5 paratypes,141.7 mm SL; B: Epigonus idai n. sp., SAIAB 204434, paratype, 132.3 mm SL." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1182179/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">Fig. 6B</figureCitation>
). In addition to the diagnostic characters, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B75AD6E624066FB8B5CFB13429FEA" authorityName="Okamoto &amp; Gon" authorityYear="2018" box="[1028,1103,224,248]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="276" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="idai">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E624066FB8B5CFB13429FEA" box="[1028,1103,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">E. idai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 20 species of the group in having 10 + 15 vertebrae (vs. 11 + 
<quantity id="4CF3A3CB6E624066FD225D1E15E79E0F" box="[685,746,260,285]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.556" pageId="15" pageNumber="276" unit="in" value="14.0">14 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="4C0B75AD6E624066FD7A5D1F14779E0E" authorityName="Okamoto" authorityYear="2012" box="[757,890,260,284]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="276" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="chilensis">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E624066FD7A5D1F14779E0E" box="[757,890,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">E. chilensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B75AD6E624066FC035D1F134C9E0E" authorityName="de Buen" authorityYear="1959" box="[908,1089,260,284]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="276" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="crassicaudus">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E624066FC035D1F134C9E0E" box="[908,1089,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">E. crassicaudus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B75AD6E624066FBDB5D1F13E99E0E" authorityName="Parin &amp; Abramov" authorityYear="1986" box="[1108,1252,260,284]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="276" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="heracleus">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E624066FBDB5D1F13E99E0E" box="[1108,1252,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">E. heracleus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B75AD6E624066FB795D1F127F9E0E" baseAuthorityName="Whitley" baseAuthorityYear="1935" box="[1270,1394,260,284]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="276" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lenimen">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E624066FB795D1F127F9E0E" box="[1270,1394,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">E. lenimen</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B75AD6E624066FA0B5D1F160A9E52" authorityName="Okamoto" authorityYear="2012" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="276" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="machaera">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E624066FA0B5D1F160A9E52" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">E. machaera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B75AD6E624066FE975D3316979E52" baseAuthorityName="Barnard" baseAuthorityYear="1927" box="[280,410,296,320]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="276" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="robustus">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E624066FE975D3316979E52" box="[280,410,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">E. robustus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), 10 soft rays on the second dorsal fin (vs. 9 soft rays in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B75AD6E624066FBC35D3313B99E52" authorityName="Parin &amp; Abramov" authorityYear="1986" box="[1100,1204,296,320]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="276" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="affinis">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E624066FBC35D3313B99E52" box="[1100,1204,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">E. affinis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B75AD6E624066FB495D3312339E52" authorityName="Parin &amp; Abramov" authorityYear="1986" box="[1222,1342,296,320]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="276" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="elegans">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E624066FB495D3312339E52" box="[1222,1342,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">E. elegans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B75AD6E624066FA0B5D33162F9E76" authorityName="Parin &amp; Abramov" authorityYear="1986" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="276" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="waltersensis">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E624066FA0B5D33162F9E76" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">E. waltersensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), 28–29 gill rakers (vs. 
<quantity id="4CF3A3CB6E624066FDA45D5615839E77" box="[555,654,332,357]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.842" metricValueMax="6.604" metricValueMin="5.08" pageId="15" pageNumber="276" unit="in" value="23.0" valueMax="26.0" valueMin="20.0">20–26 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="4C0B75AD6E624066FD1B5D5714329E76" baseAuthorityName="Gilbert" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[660,831,332,356]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="276" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="atherinoides">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E624066FD1B5D5714329E76" box="[660,831,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">E. atherinoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B75AD6E624066FCC35D5714D19E76" authorityName="Mochizuki and Shirakihara" authorityYear="1983" box="[844,988,332,356]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="276" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ctenolepis">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E624066FCC35D5714D19E76" box="[844,988,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">E. ctenolepis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B75AD6E624066FC655D5713479E76" authorityName="Okamoto" authorityYear="2015" box="[1002,1098,332,356]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="276" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="draco">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E624066FC655D5713479E76" box="[1002,1098,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">E. draco</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B75AD6E624066FBD75D5713EC9E76" authorityName="Smith &amp; Radcliffe" authorityYear="1912" box="[1112,1249,332,356]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="276" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="megalops">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E624066FBD75D5713EC9E76" box="[1112,1249,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">E. megalops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B75AD6E624066FB605D57127B9E76" authorityName="Fricke" authorityYear="2017" box="[1263,1398,332,356]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="276" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="okamotoi">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E624066FB605D57127B9E76" box="[1263,1398,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">E. okamotoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B75AD6E624066FA0B5D5716139E9A" authorityName="Goode &amp; Bean" authorityYear="1896" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="276" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="occidentalis">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E624066FA0B5D5716139E9A" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">E. occidentalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), a pair of ribs on the last abdominal vertebra (vs. absent in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B75AD6E624066FC785D6B13C79E9A" authorityName="Parin &amp; Abramov" authorityYear="1986" box="[1015,1226,368,392]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="276" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="marimonticolus">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E624066FC785D6B13C79E9A" box="[1015,1226,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">E. marimonticolus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B75AD6E624066FA865D6B12559E9A" authorityName="Prokofiev &amp; Bussarawit" authorityYear="2012" box="[1289,1368,368,392]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="276" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="thai">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E624066FA865D6B12559E9A" box="[1289,1368,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">E. thai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and lacking a pair of maxillary mustache-like processes (vs. a sharp-pointed maxillary mustache-like processes present in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B75AD6E624066FF395DA316509EDD" baseAuthorityName="Giglioli" baseAuthorityYear="1880" box="[182,349,440,464]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="276" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="constanciae">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E624066FF395DA316509EDD" box="[182,349,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">E. constanciae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B75AD6E624066FEE35DA316D69EDD" authorityName="Okamoto" authorityYear="2011" box="[364,475,440,464]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="276" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mayeri">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E624066FEE35DA316D69EDD" box="[364,475,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">E. mayeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B75AD6E624066FD925DA315A49EC2" authorityName="Mayer" authorityYear="1974" box="[541,681,440,464]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="276" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pectinifer">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E624066FD925DA315A49EC2" box="[541,681,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">E. pectinifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The diagnostic characters separating the two new species in the present study are described in the Comparison of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B75AD6E624066FD4D5DC7145A9EE6" authorityName="Okamoto &amp; Gon" authorityYear="2018" box="[706,855,476,500]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Epigonidae" genus="Epigonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="276" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bispinosus">
<emphasis id="B97FD23C6E624066FD4D5DC7145A9EE6" box="[706,855,476,500]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="276">E. bispinosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
above.
</paragraph>
